25/04/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- On Thursday (24 April), the government approved a co-operation agreement with Turkey on improving Black Sea maritime border security. The agreement was signed a week ago and stipulates joint efforts against illegal migration and the trafficking of arms, explosives, drugs, cultural artefacts, precious metals and gems. Authorities will also collaborate on initiatives against financial crimes, customs violations and international terrorism. (Dnevnik, Trud, Sega - 25/04/03; BTA, Radio Hristo Botev, BNT - 24/04/03)
